The paper deals with incremental learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The focus is on image classification, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves attention maps, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision. The paper also mentions the use of distillation loss, which is a technique used in deep learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of penalties to preserve information, which is a common technique in reinforcement learning (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
